<i>♪ I felt the wind ♪</i>

01:39.767 --> 01:43.100
<i>♪ I heard girls sing ♪</i>

01:46.233 --> 01:48.332
Come on.

01:48.333 --> 01:49.867
It's time to be a bird.

01:53.033 --> 01:54.266
Go on.

01:55.667 --> 01:57.432
Come on, get.

01:57.433 --> 01:59.599
You got your whole life ahead of you.

03:19.133 --> 03:21.266
We didn't intend to cut you out.

03:21.267 --> 03:24.099
There wasn't enough money
to go around.

03:24.100 --> 03:27.599
And this...

03:27.600 --> 03:31.199
Wasn't what we banked on.

03:31.200 --> 03:33.966
So this is plan B.

03:33.967 --> 03:35.766
And whose plan is that?

03:35.767 --> 03:37.266
We made a pact.

03:37.267 --> 03:38.999
There wasn't enough money
for our needs.

03:39.000 --> 03:42.232
We'd have to appropriate your share.

03:42.233 --> 03:44.966
Howard says it's just
a matter of priorities.

03:44.967 --> 03:47.199
Huh.
Oh, for a minute there,

03:47.200 --> 03:50.466
I thought we were just
getting screwed.

03:50.467 --> 03:52.299
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

03:52.300 --> 03:54.466
You want to keep that good eye,
keep your hand off my shit.

03:54.467 --> 03:57.099
Shut up!

03:57.100 --> 03:58.799
Does Trudy know about this?

03:58.800 --> 04:00.799
It's not personal, Hap.

04:00.800 --> 04:04.366
Oh, good, good.

04:04.367 --> 04:07.067
What is it, then?

04:08.567 --> 04:11.000
Sacrifice.

04:50.900 --> 04:54.199
Speed it up.

04:54.200 --> 04:58.066
At this rate,
we'll be here all night.

04:58.067 --> 04:59.367
Come on.

05:01.967 --> 05:04.599
Who the hell buries money anyway?

05:04.600 --> 05:06.999
Y'all been reading
too many damn caper books.

05:07.000 --> 05:09.166
With all these cops around,
it's called being smart.

05:09.167 --> 05:10.699
Maybe you two ought to
try it some time.

05:10.700 --> 05:13.099
If you're so smart,

05:13.100 --> 05:15.699
why are you burying this
in front of us?

05:16.967 --> 05:19.832
- Hey!
- Hey, hey, hey.

05:19.833 --> 05:22.332
It's an awful lot of
rough housing for a peacenik.

05:22.333 --> 05:23.398
Now, look, you had that coming.

05:23.399 --> 05:24.865
Ow.

05:24.867 --> 05:26.199
Look, I never said
I was against violence.

05:26.200 --> 05:28.432
Sometimes the ends justify the means.

05:28.433 --> 05:30.099
All right?

05:30.100 --> 05:32.699
So why don't you come over
here and try that on me?

05:32.700 --> 05:35.032
Shove that gun so far up your ass

05:35.033 --> 05:38.232
you's taste gunpowder.

05:38.233 --> 05:39.767
Come on!

05:47.533 --> 05:50.732
Chub,

05:50.733 --> 05:53.733
put the box in the hole.

05:59.500 --> 06:01.800
Go ahead.
I got it.

06:13.267 --> 06:15.132
All right, Leonard.

06:15.133 --> 06:17.099
You fill it in.

06:17.100 --> 06:19.732
Pretend it's a rose bush
or something,

06:19.733 --> 06:21.499
whatever the hell you two do
for work--

06:21.500 --> 06:23.266
- they got fired.
- All right.

06:23.267 --> 06:27.166
Whatever--you know,
whatever you did for work.

06:27.167 --> 06:29.232
So this how y'all do, huh?

06:29.233 --> 06:32.232
All peaceful-like.

06:32.233 --> 06:34.666
Get your gun up.

06:34.667 --> 06:36.633
Hey.

06:38.333 --> 06:42.532
Look like you gonna
have to use that thing, Howard.

06:42.533 --> 06:45.632
Ever kill a man before?

06:45.633 --> 06:47.833
I did.

06:51.667 --> 06:54.133
Paco, fill it in.

06:57.433 --> 07:01.299
These fellers have stepped
in the wrong pile of shit.

07:01.300 --> 07:03.066
Let's not rub it in.

07:03.067 --> 07:04.799
They've been riding me
since they got here.

07:04.800 --> 07:06.366
If I'd have known I was coming...

07:06.367 --> 07:08.399
Hey.

07:09.967 --> 07:12.967
I'd have ridden you a hell of
a lot harder.

07:40.500 --> 07:42.199
This is everything.

07:42.200 --> 07:45.200
This is--this is the total.

07:48.500 --> 07:50.332
The rest is unusable.

07:50.333 --> 07:52.899
Well, it's--
it's not enough.

07:52.900 --> 07:54.699
If we're smart about things,
efficient,

07:54.700 --> 07:56.166
no more mistakes from here on out.

07:56.167 --> 07:58.466
Y'all already made one mistake:

07:58.467 --> 08:00.967
Pissing me off!

08:08.233 --> 08:10.932
You gonna use that, chub?

08:10.933 --> 08:14.699
Just let us do our thing.
We'll let you go.

08:14.700 --> 08:17.066
Howard doesn't want anybody
to know about us yet.

08:17.067 --> 08:18.599
You ain't got to worry
about me telling nobody.

08:18.600 --> 08:20.132
No, sir.

08:20.133 --> 08:21.832
Think I want the world to know
I got suckered

08:21.833 --> 08:24.132
by a bunch of idiots?

08:24.133 --> 08:27.432
What is this thing?

08:27.433 --> 08:30.366
You zip it, chub.

08:30.367 --> 08:33.000
Not supposed to say.

08:37.933 --> 08:39.466
Come on.

08:39.467 --> 08:41.633
Who we gonna tell, the couch?

08:55.467 --> 08:57.566
We're gonna buy some drugs.

08:57.567 --> 08:58.567
Oh.

08:58.568 --> 09:00.566
What, like, like grass?

09:00.567 --> 09:02.532
- Uh-uh, cocaine.
- Cocaine?

09:02.533 --> 09:03.932
<i>- Chub!
- Chub!</i>

09:03.933 --> 09:05.232
You stupid shit.

09:05.233 --> 09:06.599
All right, okay.

09:06.600 --> 09:08.266
What the hell does buying cocaine

09:08.267 --> 09:11.332
have to do with making
a difference to this world, huh?

09:11.333 --> 09:13.566
That wasn't part of
the big pitch you sold me.

09:13.567 --> 09:15.566
If we're gonna launch
a sustainable movement,

09:15.567 --> 09:19.732
we need sustainable income.

09:19.733 --> 09:22.099
They're gonna use cocaine
to fund their cause.

09:22.100 --> 09:27.099
How do you think the mechanics
survived as long as we did?

09:27.100 --> 09:30.432
By selling sweet Mary Jane
to college students.

09:30.433 --> 09:31.832
Cocaine's a bit different.

09:31.833 --> 09:33.699
- Don't you think?
- Exactly.

09:33.700 --> 09:36.032
- Who buys cocaine?
- Cokeheads, mostly.

09:36.033 --> 09:37.532
People who can afford it.

09:37.533 --> 09:39.366
It's a luxury drug.

09:39.367 --> 09:41.399
Consider us a luxury tax.

09:41.400 --> 09:43.099
We're gonna take it from the rich,

09:43.100 --> 09:45.032
and we're gonna use it
to help the people that need it.

09:45.033 --> 09:46.899
Like Robin hood.

09:46.900 --> 09:49.232
Last I remember, little John
didn't have no pager.

09:49.233 --> 09:51.932
Y'all just a bunch of goddamn
drug dealers.

09:51.933 --> 09:54.599
No, no, we use the system
to beat the system,

09:54.600 --> 09:56.332
and then we change the system.

09:56.333 --> 09:58.399
You can beat my meat and
preach about the system

09:58.400 --> 09:59.666
and the seals all you want--

09:59.667 --> 10:01.499
who said anything about the seals?

10:01.500 --> 10:02.666
What's with the seals?
Why does he keep saying that?

10:02.667 --> 10:04.232
Whales, elephants, whatever.

10:04.233 --> 10:06.832
You know what happens
to drug dealers, hmm?

10:06.833 --> 10:10.232
They end up in prison or in a ditch

10:10.233 --> 10:12.066
with a bullet in the head.

10:12.067 --> 10:13.932
Actually, that don't sound
like a bad idea.

10:13.933 --> 10:15.566
Paco's done this before.

10:15.567 --> 10:17.332
He's got the connections.

10:17.333 --> 10:20.033
Yeah, look at him now.

10:22.267 --> 10:25.066
They handle the traffic.
We handle the income.

10:25.067 --> 10:26.299
We stay clean.

10:26.300 --> 10:28.099
Yeah, and then we have the power.

10:28.100 --> 10:30.166
Power?

10:30.167 --> 10:31.999
You lost your drawers in the swamp.

10:32.000 --> 10:33.866
What the hell you gonna do
with any damn power?

10:33.867 --> 10:36.099
What makes you think we need
an economics lesson

10:36.100 --> 10:37.832
from two out-of-work
field hands?

10:37.833 --> 10:42.232
Technically, we're rosarians,
not field hands.

10:42.233 --> 10:44.066
You two ain't thought
this shit out, did you?

10:44.067 --> 10:45.532
Ignore him, Trudy.

10:45.533 --> 10:46.899
You might have saved
a couple of lives,

10:46.900 --> 10:48.366
but you're gonna ruin a bunch more.

10:48.367 --> 10:49.999
Think them drugs just gonna
reach the hands

10:50.000 --> 10:51.532
of some Hollywood big shot
or up the nose

10:51.533 --> 10:53.732
of some wall street scumbag?

10:53.733 --> 10:55.232
They're gonna end up on the street

10:55.233 --> 10:57.166
in the hands of some kids
don't even know

10:57.167 --> 10:58.167
what they hell they doing.

10:58.168 --> 10:59.499
Don't listen to him.

10:59.500 --> 11:01.032
He's just being derisive.

11:01.033 --> 11:03.266
- Oh, that's a big word...
- Quiet.

11:03.267 --> 11:05.199
For such a little asshole to fart.

11:05.200 --> 11:07.267
All right, that's enough.

11:17.433 --> 11:19.633
That was impressive.

11:21.267 --> 11:23.567
You rehearse that?

11:25.800 --> 11:28.032
Nice girlfriend you got there.

11:28.033 --> 11:31.366
Got more faces than a diamond.

11:31.367 --> 11:33.999
Okay.

11:34.000 --> 11:36.599
I admit that.

11:36.600 --> 11:39.899
That took me by surprise.

11:39.900 --> 11:42.299
And here we are,

11:42.300 --> 11:45.799
gun in face,
duct-taped to a chair.

11:45.800 --> 11:47.766
Mm, mm, mm.

11:47.767 --> 11:50.699
Glider.

11:50.700 --> 11:52.166
What?

11:52.167 --> 11:53.999
- It's a glider.
- It's my damn porch.

11:54.000 --> 11:55.599
- I know what it is.
- Just saying.

11:55.600 --> 11:59.100
You said enough,
talking me into this mess.

12:06.867 --> 12:09.033
- My nose itches.
- I don't care.

13:31.333 --> 13:33.532
Oh, shit.

13:33.533 --> 13:36.866
Shit.

14:14.433 --> 14:19.132
Maybe we didn't
think this through enough.

14:19.133 --> 14:23.200
It's a little late to start
second-guessing ourselves.

14:24.533 --> 14:27.433
I thought this was what we wanted.

14:29.600 --> 14:32.099
Of course it is, babe.

14:32.100 --> 14:34.399
Of course.

14:34.400 --> 14:37.666
I just want us to stay sharp.

14:37.667 --> 14:39.599
We've never done anything
like this before.

14:39.600 --> 14:41.800
Paco has.

14:43.867 --> 14:45.332
What if they're right?

14:45.333 --> 14:47.566
Don't let them get to you.

14:47.567 --> 14:52.666
We have to play the game
if we're gonna survive.

14:52.667 --> 14:54.866
I'm not letting anyone get to me.

14:54.867 --> 14:56.199
I'm just asking.

14:56.200 --> 14:58.332
All right.

14:58.333 --> 15:01.099
Is this who we are?

15:01.100 --> 15:03.032
It's like you say.

15:03.033 --> 15:06.267
"The right path isn't
always the easy one."

15:35.233 --> 15:37.832
I didn't know it was
gonna turn out like this, guys.

15:37.833 --> 15:40.732
I feel terrible.

15:40.733 --> 15:43.800
I'm really sorry,
for what it's worth.

15:52.000 --> 15:54.566
Do you want anything?

15:54.567 --> 15:56.766
I want to take back
saving your fat ass

15:56.767 --> 15:58.967
in the swamp.

16:03.300 --> 16:06.499
They don't respect you.
You know that, right?

16:06.500 --> 16:08.999
They see you, they see a
walking, talking pork chop,

16:09.000 --> 16:10.532
same as us.

16:10.533 --> 16:11.999
Only thing, they ain't gonna
slaughter you

16:12.000 --> 16:14.999
like they gonna do us.

16:15.000 --> 16:18.067
I'm not gonna let that happen.

16:20.800 --> 16:23.400
I understand your anger.

16:26.167 --> 16:29.133
You could never understand
my anger.

16:35.333 --> 16:37.833
Chub.

16:39.767 --> 16:42.500
Are we getting out of here?

16:46.167 --> 16:49.099
Howard said that he--

16:49.100 --> 16:52.699
he'll drop you guys off
at the state line tomorrow

16:52.700 --> 16:54.032
after we meet Paco's guy.

16:54.033 --> 16:56.132
Chub.

16:56.133 --> 16:58.167
Inside.

17:32.467 --> 17:34.799
<i>Dear Hap,</i>

17:34.800 --> 17:35.932
<i>it's been awhile.</i>

17:35.933 --> 17:37.999
<i>I know.</i>

17:38.000 --> 17:40.866
<i>I keep meaning to visit, but...</i>

17:40.867 --> 17:44.999
<i>I never have been great at life.</i>

17:45.000 --> 17:48.266
<i>I think of you often, though,
you in there,</i>

17:48.267 --> 17:52.866
<i>making a difference, dedicated.</i>

17:52.867 --> 17:57.232
<i>And me, out here,</i>

17:57.233 --> 17:59.399
<i>it's quiet, Hap.</i>

17:59.400 --> 18:01.232
<i>I keep thinking it'll get easier,</i>

18:01.233 --> 18:07.266
<i>but then I remember,
that's not how the world works.</i>

18:07.267 --> 18:10.899
<i>And I'm never one to sit still,
so I've decided</i>

18:10.900 --> 18:13.899
<i>to do something about it,
to try and make a difference</i>

18:13.900 --> 18:16.699
<i>of my own.</i>

18:16.700 --> 18:19.499
<i>I've moved to San Francisco.</i>

18:19.500 --> 18:23.799
<i>It's a long way,
but it really is for the best,</i>

18:23.800 --> 18:28.732
<i>for me, for the cause.</i>

18:28.733 --> 18:31.299
<i>I've joined a group of people
out here.</i>

18:31.300 --> 18:33.766
<i>We march and protest against the war,</i>

18:33.767 --> 18:36.332
<i>like we used to do.</i>

18:36.333 --> 18:41.066
<i>Feels good, you know,
to be a part of something.</i>

18:41.067 --> 18:43.366
<i>You know what they say.</i>

18:43.367 --> 18:47.532
<i>Some things are just meant to be.</i>

18:47.533 --> 18:49.766
<i>I've told them about you
and what you're doing</i>

18:49.767 --> 18:52.632
<i>to make a stand.</i>

18:52.633 --> 18:55.432
<i>I'm so proud of you, honey.</i>

18:55.433 --> 18:57.966
<i>I love you.</i>

18:57.967 --> 19:03.166
<i>Always did, always will.</i>

19:03.167 --> 19:05.000
<i>Trudy.</i>

19:18.967 --> 19:21.266
You smoke now too, huh?

19:21.267 --> 19:26.299
Boy, you are just full of surprises.

19:26.300 --> 19:28.499
Only when I'm nervous.

19:28.500 --> 19:31.899
Oh, you are.
Hey, it could be worse.

19:31.900 --> 19:34.700
You could be duct-taped
to a glider.

19:39.333 --> 19:42.532
Want to tell me what's going on?

19:42.533 --> 19:45.799
I would if I thought it would
make you feel better.

19:45.800 --> 19:50.066
Not too late to change your mind.

19:50.067 --> 19:52.066
Call it off.

19:52.067 --> 19:54.366
Let us go.

19:54.367 --> 19:58.332
Take your share and run away.

19:58.333 --> 19:59.666
You've done it before.

19:59.667 --> 20:02.799
I'm done running.

20:02.800 --> 20:06.132
This is my chance.
I'm taking it.

20:06.133 --> 20:09.499
No matter who it hurts?

20:09.500 --> 20:13.332
I gave you every opportunity
to be a part of this.

20:13.333 --> 20:17.866
You made your choice.

20:17.867 --> 20:21.199
Somebody always gets hurt, Hap.

20:21.200 --> 20:25.132
This time, the greater good
will win out.

20:25.133 --> 20:28.299
Greater good?

20:28.300 --> 20:30.732
There was a time when

20:30.733 --> 20:33.866
that meant protesting against wars

20:33.867 --> 20:38.000
and marching for equality, not this.

20:39.933 --> 20:42.632
You remember those two monks
who set themselves on fire

20:42.633 --> 20:44.132
to protest the war?

20:44.133 --> 20:46.432
Mm.

20:46.433 --> 20:48.299
I want that kind of dedication.

20:48.300 --> 20:51.166
Oh, they were dedicated, all right.

20:51.167 --> 20:53.632
They also got burned up.

20:53.633 --> 20:57.067
I need to believe in something.

21:00.833 --> 21:03.066
I've done a lot of things in my life.

21:03.067 --> 21:06.933
I've failed at almost all of them.

21:08.767 --> 21:11.467
I don't have another
failure in me, Hap.

21:13.533 --> 21:16.067
Even if it means this?

21:18.200 --> 21:20.233
Try and get some sleep.

21:54.567 --> 21:57.333
About time you woke up.

22:01.700 --> 22:05.166
We on speaking terms again, then?

22:10.300 --> 22:12.266
He came out here over an hour ago.

22:12.267 --> 22:14.232
Howard told him to keep an eye on us.

22:16.933 --> 22:19.132
Doing a pretty shitty job of it.

22:19.133 --> 22:21.633
You think?

22:23.567 --> 22:26.499
Let's go.

22:26.500 --> 22:29.099
Go?
Where?

22:29.100 --> 22:31.132
Let's get out of here.

22:31.133 --> 22:32.432
How?

22:32.433 --> 22:33.999
Get on your feet.

22:34.000 --> 22:35.599
We're gonna walk this thing
out to the woods

22:35.600 --> 22:36.766
and get it off us.

22:36.767 --> 22:38.366
Make a run for it.

22:38.367 --> 22:40.800
- You crazy?
- You got a better idea?

22:43.533 --> 22:45.166
Shouldn't we have
done this last night?

22:45.167 --> 22:47.632
I didn't think of it last night.

22:47.633 --> 22:50.466
Now, come on.
You with me?

22:50.467 --> 22:51.433
Okay.

22:51.434 --> 22:54.099
On three.

22:54.100 --> 22:57.367
One, two, three.

23:05.567 --> 23:07.232
Shh, shh, shh.

23:09.533 --> 23:11.166
You're going too fast.

23:11.167 --> 23:13.566
We're going too fast.

23:13.567 --> 23:15.532
You shut up.

23:22.033 --> 23:24.033
Just give me five.
Give me five.

23:26.700 --> 23:28.432
Come on, now we're making progress.

23:28.433 --> 23:29.666
Ready?
Let's go.

23:29.667 --> 23:31.666
Yeah, come on.

23:31.667 --> 23:33.366
Could we just slow down?

23:33.367 --> 23:34.599
You're tripping on my toes.

23:34.600 --> 23:35.932
Bitch, bitch, bitch.

23:35.933 --> 23:37.499
Stepping on my damn corn.

23:37.500 --> 23:39.966
- Just slow down.
- We ain't going slower.

23:39.967 --> 23:41.332
We're going backwards.

23:41.333 --> 23:43.566
Come on, this ain't so hard, is it?

